.TH ID_VERSION 1 "June 2026" "mx-remaster" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
id_version \- generate a simple version-style identifier string
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B id_version
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B id_version
prints a randomly generated identifier in a version-like form.
The output consists of the literal prefix
.B ====
followed by two random hexadecimal strings.
It is a small helper used by the remaster and version-file workflows when a
unique-looking identifier is needed.
.SH OPTIONS
.B id_version
accepts no options.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR live-remaster (1),
.BR installed-to-live (1)
.SH AUTHOR
mx-remaster maintainers
